OL,3,CThe two men now expected to lead
OL,4,CLabour both ends of the M4
OL,6,FFor First Minister Rhun ap Iorwerth,
OL,7,Fhe believes the 'chaos' in Westminster
OL,8,Fhas meant Wales is at a disadvantage
OL,9,Fin the world of politics.
OL,11,FUntil the new UK Prime Minister is
OL,12,Fsolidified, then the real work between
OL,13,Fthe Welsh and UK Governments can begin.
OL,15,FAlex Davies-Jones, the Pontypridd
OL,16,FLabour MP is looking ahead brightly to
OL,17,Fthe change in leadership, and believes
OL,18,Fthat Burnham will "be the one that
OL,19,Flistens" to the people of Wales.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/6
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
